h day is not a viable option. It would create even more bad-blood on the server than is currently present, and chances are good that both guilds could happen to be in the plane at the same time and with GM's who knows what happens..<br>
<br>
Though, convoluted as hell, something along the lines of a linked-list for members of epic guilds.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of posting entities currently on the calendar, but I'd bet there's at least 5-8 that have members that aren't anywhere close to finishing or even starting their epics yet can bring down a God.<br>
<br>
Depending on the epic quest (queen in chardok hmm) [difficulty rating] would it be possible to setup something &quot;like&quot; 'need-before-greed' (though most who disagree would probably see it as greed-before-need)? <br>
<br>
XYGuild (POH) can't use item_001, calls XYEpicGuild on rotation, XYEpicGuild obtains item_001 and is moved to bottom of rotation.<br>
<br>
Now what to do about Epic's &quot;piggybacking&quot;<br>
Epic Banana Guild decides to go with GuildPeanuts who could probably kill a God on their own but has zero use for the item(s) so they decide to give them to Epic Banana Guild. Epic Banana Guild loses their next plane date (POH in this case) and is dumped to the bottom of the Epic rotation and cannot re-reserve POH for up-to one week, OR on Epic Banana Guild's up and coming POH raid if a God is up they must call whomever was at the top of the rotation on GuildPeanuts' day.<br>
Of course if Epic Banana Guild gets a God on their own plane date and did not 'break' the above guideline more power to them.<br>
<br>
<br>
Or something like that.. hmm.<br>
